data.text:
March 30, 1956 was a Friday and it was the 90th day of the year 1956 in the Gregorian calendar.

March 30, 1956 can also be written as 3/30/1956 in the US and as 30/3/1956 in UK and Europe.

The Zodiac and Astrological sign for March 30th is Aries.

Aries is the 1st sign in the Western Zodiac. People born between March 21st and April 19th belong to the Aries sign: discover Aries personality and who should a Aries marry.

Babies born in March are either Pisces or Aries. People born before March 20th are Pisces, while people born from March 21st have the sign of Aries.

Moon phase

The moon phase on March 30, 1956 was Waning gibbous.

The moon phase refers to the appearance of the Moon in the night sky on March 30, 1956 and is determined by the portion of the Moon's illuminated surface that is visible from Earth.

An observer located in New York City on March 30, 1956 at 10pm, would see the moon, being 75% full, rising at 09:58 pm and setting at 08:34 am.

The previous full moon was on Mar 26, 1956 while the next full moon would come on Apr 25, 1956.

What is special about March 30th?

March 30th refers to a specific date on the calendar, which is the 30th day of the month of March. It is a date that occurs annually and is part of the Gregorian calendar, which is widely used around the world.

Over the years several events happened on March 30th, such as:

2019 - War in afghanistan: abdul rashid dostum, the first vice president of afghanistan, survives an attack on his convoy as he travels to jowzjan province in afghanistan. one bodyguard was killed and two other were injured in the attack.

2018 - Terrorism is in pakistan: three people are killed and five more injured by a bomb that was dropped on police officers in dera ismail khan (pakistan).

2017 - Syrian civil war: according the united nations high commission for refugees (unhcr), syria has more than five million refugees.
